"transcript": "If you struggle with what to clean, when to clean it, not knowing where to start so you don't even clean anything, you're probably like most people. And that is, all it needs is a system. I teach you the system for keeping your home clean. It's minutes a day. It can be done on any schedule, regardless of if you work from home, if you work outside of the home, if you're a stay-at-home parent. You can do the system with a couple minutes a day. So daily tasks. There's five of them. Simple. You're probably already doing them. You're probably just not assigning them as a daily task. Weekly tasks. Monday, bathroom stay. Tuesday, dusty. There's something every single day of the week. You just keep that on the system. If you miss something, there's a day built in so that you can catch up. Makes it really easy. Also allows for life to happen. Check it out. Comment guide so I can teach you my system and you can get back to your life.", "history": [{"date": "2026-07-18", "plays": 11372, "likes": 121, "comments": 135}], "still_climbing": false}]}